resolvedData.name: dateModified
resolvedData.description: Last date/time of object modification. Mandatory if applicable. (context : KernelInformation)

resolvedData.name: license
resolvedData.description: names license requirement of the collection (type : string, currently, but could be also given as a controlled vocabulary, like '["CC0", "CC-BY", "CC-BY-SA", "CC-by-NC", "CC-BY-ND", "CC-BY-NC-SA", "CC-BY-NC-ND"]', context : collection).

resolvedData.name: dateCreatedRfc3339
resolvedData.description: This datatype uses the same format as dateModified for a creation date. This makes implementation for clients easier, especially since this format is well supported by libraries.

standards.name: 21.T11148/3bfb2839a6967114bc3e
standards.details: Format representing date and time, which is well supported by libraries.

standards.name: 21.T11148/397d831aa3a9d18eb52c
standards.details: dateModified. The semantix is similar, the syntax is even the same, which is the reason for this type.

contributors.name: Andreas Pfeil
contributors.details: Andreas Pfeil, Karlsruhe Institute of Technology

expectedUses: Use this to have the same date-time-format in your schemes for dateModified and dateCreated.

resolvedData.name: version
resolvedData.description: If tracked, a version for the object, which must follow a total order. Mandatory for all objects with at least one predecessor version. (context : PID_Kernel_Information)

resolvedData.name: etag
resolvedData.description: Checksum of object contents. Checksum format determined via attribute type referenced in a Kernel Information record. (context : KernelInformation)

resolvedData.name: digitalObjectLocation
resolvedData.description: Pointer to the content object location (pointer to the DO). This may be in addition to a pointer to ahuman-readable landing page for the object. (context : KernelInformation)

resolvedData.name: isMetadataFor
resolvedData.description: A PID pointing to another FAIR DO describing the digital object.

contributors.name: Andreas Pfeil
contributors.details: Andreas Pfeil, Karlsruhe Institute of Technology

expectedUses: It offers the possibility to link related FDOs to each other, e.g., to build up a FDO graph easily. Furthermore, it allows to find data belonging to a metadata-focussed object. With regard to machine-actionability this property allows to decide, whether a sufficient amount of metadata is available in order to interpret associated data for a certain use case.

resolvedData.name: genericObjectType
resolvedData.description: A profile often contains an object type, but a datatype is not always referencable by a pid. Therefore, this experiment tries to expand the possibilities.

contributors.name: Andreas Pfeil

representationsAndSemantics.details: Repeatable in case a data type conforms to more than one format at once. Example: .drawio.png extension conforms to .png and .drawio.

resolvedData.name: KernelInformationProfile
resolvedData.description: Handle to the Kernel Information type profile; serves as pointer to profile in DTR. Address of DTR federation expected to be global (common) knowledge. (context : KernelInformation)

resolvedData.name: contact
resolvedData.description: A web-resolvable pointer to an institution or a person responsible for the digital object.

contributors.name: Andreas Pfeil
contributors.details: Andreas Pfeil, Karlsruhe Institute of Technology

expectedUses: Increases trust in the data, as there is someone who can be contacted if any questions about the data arise.
